<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Reserved by the <em>Great Reservio!!</em> Yes, I am more enthusiastic here than in the other entry, what of it?</span></p>
<p>Woah, what a doozy! Been more than a month since I reserved this post, and now I am finally writing it. Alright! So, I decided to write this after addressing Conwell's critiques &#8212; I feel I have made this course of action more believable than perhaps it once was. Now, I am <em>super</em> happy to have worked with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ellie3" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3656445); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3656445&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1563838325" alt="Ellie3" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3656445)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ellie3" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3656445); return false;">Ellie3</a></span> for this contest, and producing some more WWS content (I love writing out some sweet sweet WWS <em>lore</em>). This came about once we realized that there was no story on the site about how WWS had acquired an adoption center in Three Ports. Now, I know that the Adoption Poster articles have had Tim Wilson be around, but canon shmanon, this is how it be in my world.</p>
<p>Became close pals with Ellie through this contest, which is a bigger win than any number of upvotes, so very glad that this happened :3</p>

