<blockquote>
<p>That said, the idea of carting potentially dangerous anomalous animals into a major population center (still necessary for using ways into Three Ports) is a bit contrived, and the means of keeping this quiet still not elaborated enough to my taste. Vote changed to neutral.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>But&#8230;</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>My favorite part about this property is that it's close to a Way, which I could, well, &quot;hijack&quot; makes it sound so brutish, but you get the idea. Said Way is also relatively low traffic, making this location the cheapest and fastest to transport to and from.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>I guess I didn't spell it out so clearly, but that's because Ellie and I were struggling with where to fit it into the article &#8212; the idea is that Capital R is making a covert way from Boring, Oregon to Three Portlands, to avoid going through Portland, Oregon directly. Do inform me, whether this is even possible, but my headcanon says that a Way can be made from anywhere to anywhere else, with powerful enough magic.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The meeting with Capital R was successful and WWS is now in possession of the property <span style="text-decoration: underline;">and an associated Way</span>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Like, I doubt Wilson's could literally own one of <em>the</em> 3Ports Ways in Portland, Oregon.</p>

